values.name: CustomSingleLabelClassification
values.doc: For building a classification model to classify text using your own data. Each file will have only one label. For example, file 1 is classified as A and file 2 is classified as B.

values.name: CustomMultiLabelClassification
values.doc: For building a classification model to classify text using your own data. Each file can have one or many labels. For example, file 1 is classified as A, B, and C and file 2 is classified as B and C.

values.name: CustomEntityRecognition
values.doc: For building an extraction model to identify your domain categories using your own data.

values.name: CustomAbstractiveSummarization
values.doc: For building an abstractive summarization models which are able to summarize long documents.

values.name: CustomHealthcare
values.doc: For building an text analytics for health model to identify your health domain data.

values.name: CustomTextSentiment
values.doc: For building a sentiment models which are able to extract sentiment for long documents.

values.name: Utf16CodeUnit
values.doc: The offset and length values will correspond to UTF-16 code units. Use this option if your application is written in a language that support Unicode, for example Java, JavaScript.

values.name: separateComponents
values.doc: Every component's match or prediction is returned as a separate instance of the entity.

values.name: combineComponents
values.doc: When two or more components are found in the text and overlap, the components' spans are merged together into one span combining all of them.

values.name: percentage
values.doc: Split the data into training and test sets according to user-defined percentages.

values.name: manual
values.doc: Split the data according to the chosen dataset for every example in the data.

Clients.Name: AuthoringClient
Clients.Doc: The language service API is a suite of natural language processing (NLP) skills built with best-in-class Microsoft machine learning algorithms. The API can be used to analyze unstructured text for tasks such as sentiment analysis, key phrase extraction, language detection and question answering. Further documentation can be found in https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cognitive-services/language-service/overview.
